race.comment: FIRE ISLAND (5) led and folded up at Kembla Grange, but her wet track form at that venue prior reads well enough for this. In a top Sydney yard and is an each-way chance to knock off the firm favourite. TSARINA DIAMONDS (8) has switched to the Kelley yard on a 32-day return. Brings strong Victorian form this distance range and she's a leader drawn to advantage. Expect her to be tuned up for the stable's race-day and go close. POKER FLASH (2) won her Maiden here comfortably and the lightly-raced mare is much improved. Keeps the 2kg claim and is well in the mix. SO SUPERIOR (3) starts here instead of Kembla Grange tomorrow. Found more like her best placing at Goulburn and will improve off that.
